<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q19_v8" title="Porcentaje compuesto sobre 100" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>Se aplica dos veces consecutivas un factor de 0,8 a la cantidad 100, es decir, en cada paso se multiplica la cantidad por 0,8.</p>
    <p>¿Cuál de las siguientes alternativas indica correctamente qué porcentaje de 100 representa el valor final?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-Choices="1">
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">80 %<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Aplicar el factor 0,8 dos veces da 100 × 0,8 = 80 y luego 80 × 0,8 = 64. Por lo tanto, el valor final representa 64 % de 100, no 80 %.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">64 %<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Al aplicar dos veces el factor 0,8 se obtiene 100 × 0,8 = 80 y después 80 × 0,8 = 64. Entonces el valor final es 64 de 100, es decir, 64 %.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">160 %<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Aplicar el factor 0,8 dos veces no aumenta la cantidad: 100 × 0,8 = 80 y 80 × 0,8 = 64. El resultado final es 64 de 100, o sea 64 %, no 160 %.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">6400 %<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. El valor final se calcula como 100 × 0,8 × 0,8 = 100 × 0,64 = 64. Como 64 representa 64 de 100, el porcentaje es 64 %, no 6400 %.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Aplicar el factor 0,8 una primera vez</strong></p>
            <p>Partimos de 100. Multiplicamos por 0,8:</p>
            <p>
              <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                <mrow>
                  <mn>100</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0,8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>80</mn>
                </mrow>
              </math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Aplicar el factor 0,8 una segunda vez</strong></p>
            <p>Ahora multiplicamos nuevamente por 0,8:</p>
            <p>
              <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                <mrow>
                  <mn>80</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0,8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>64</mn>
                </mrow>
              </math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Interpretar 64 como porcentaje de 100</strong></p>
            <p>El valor final es 64, y eso corresponde a 64 de cada 100.</p>
            <p>
              <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                <mrow>
                  <mn>64</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>%</mo><mtext> de </mtext><mn>100</mn>
                </mrow>
              </math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Verificación con el factor total</strong></p>
            <p>También se puede multiplicar los factores primero:</p>
            <p>
              <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                <mrow>
                  <mn>0,8</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0,8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0,64</mn>
                </mrow>
              </math>
            </p>
            <p>Entonces:</p>
            <p>
              <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                <mrow>
                  <mn>100</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0,64</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>64</mn>
                </mrow>
              </math>
            </p>
            <p>Eso confirma que el valor final representa 64 % de 100.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La alternativa correcta es <strong>64 %</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>